---
title: Spanish Steak Salad with Red Pepper & Roasted Garlic Vinaigrette
description: Oven roasting transforms pungent garlic into a sweet, mellow ingredient that improves just about everything. Here, garlic and rosemary are roasted together to create the base for a killer vinaigrette. When drizzled over sliced steak, roasted red peppers, and tangy goat cheese, salads don't get much better than this.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/54ecd65d6ced6e44738b4569.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/54ecd65d6ced6e44738b4569.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 764 kcal
  fat: 45 g
  carbohydrates: 39 g
  protein: 53 g
  fiber: 6 g
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/spanish-steak-salad-54ecd65d6ced6e44738b4569
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: Spanish
servings: 2
---

Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Remove @sirloin steak{12%ounce} from fridge and allow to come to room temperature. Strip the leaves from the @rosemary{1%sprig}. Crush the @garlic{2%cloves} with the back of your knife. Core, seed, and remove the white veins from @red bell pepper{1}, then thinly slice. Toss the bell pepper on a #baking sheet{} with @olive oil{1/2%tablespoon} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Wrap the garlic and rosemary in #foil{} with @olive oil{1/2%tablespoon}. Place foil bundle on the baking sheet with the peppers. Roast for ~{15%minutes}, tossing peppers halfway through.

Heat @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a medium #oven-proof pan{} over medium high-heat. Pat the steak dry with #paper towels{} and season with salt and pepper on both sides. Cook for ~{2-3%minutes} per side, or until golden brown. Transfer pan to the oven and roast for ~{6-8%minutes}, or until cooked to desired doneness. Set aside to rest.

> HINT: If you don't have an oven-proof pan, just transfer the steak to the baking sheet to finish!

Cut the @baguette{1} into 1/2-inch slices on a diagonal. Place the bread on a baking sheet, drizzle with @olive oil{}, and toast for ~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, once the garlic is softened, mash with a #fork{} to form a paste. Coarsely chop the rosemary leaves. To make the dressing, whisk together roasted garlic, rosemary, @white wine vinegar{1%tablespoon}, and @olive oil{2%tablespoons} in a #medium bowl{}. Season with salt and pepper.

Toss the @mixed greens{2%ounce} in the dressing with the roasted peppers. Thinly slice the steak against the grain and arrange over a bed of the greens. Top with the @crumbled goat cheese{1/4%cup} and serve with baguette toasts to the side.